<div>This guy got there going up and over from Hell Hole: Hell Hole - Seidner Lake | Utah Wildlife Forum. Dan Potts puts this in his list of 5 must-visit lakes. “Park at the Christmas Meadows Trailhead out of Kamas. Although it is less than a five-mile hike, the last two miles gain 1,500 feet! The side drainage leading to the lake is easy to reach and spot on the right about one and a half miles up the Christmas Meadows Trail. This lake is where I set my record of landing 27 brook trout on consecutive casts, although they were all small. This is a lake for those who are fit and really want to get away from it all.” https://utahstories.com/2021/08/the-top-five-lakes-in-the-high-uinta-mountains-to-visit/<br></div>
